10_1	<div class="c10_1">
10_1	<div id="v10.1.1"><span class="H7225 s">In the beginning</span><span class="H430 s"> God</span><span class="H1254 s"> created</span><span class="H853 s"> †</span><span class="H8064 s"> the heaven</span><span class="H853 s"> and</span><span class="H776 s"> the earth</span>.</div>
10_1	<div id="v10.1.2"><span class="H776 s">And the earth</span><span class="H1961 s"> was</span><span class="H8414 s"> without form</span><span class="H922 s">, and void</span><span class="H2822 s">; and darkness</span><span class="H6440 s"> <i>was</i> upon the face</span><span class="H8415 s"> of the deep</span><span class="H7307 s">. And the Spirit</span><span class="H430 s"> of God</span><span class="H7363 s"> moved</span><span class="H5921 s"> upon</span><span class="H6440 s"> the face</span><span class="H4325 s"> of the waters</span>.</div>
10_1	<div id="v10.1.3"><span class="H430 s">And God</span><span class="H559 s"> said</span><span class="H1961 s">, Let there be</span><span class="H216 s"> light</span><span class="H216 s">: and there was light</span>.</div>
10_1	<div id="v10.1.4"><span class="H430 s">And God</span><span class="H7200 s"> saw</span><span class="H853 s"> †</span><span class="H216 s"> the light</span><span class="H3588 s">, that</span><span class="H2896 s"> <i>it was</i> good</span><span class="H430 s">: and God</span><span class="H914 s"> divided</span><span class="H996 s"> †</span><span class="H216 s"> the light</span><span class="H996 s"> from</span><span class="H2822 s"> the darkness</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (the light from…: Heb. between the light and between the darkness)</span></div>
10_1	<div id="v10.1.5"><span class="H430 s">And God</span><span class="H7121 s"> called</span><span class="H216 s"> the light</span><span class="H3117 s"> Day</span><span class="H2822 s">, and the darkness</span><span class="H7121 s"> he called</span><span class="H3915 s"> Night</span><span class="H6153 s">. And the evening</span><span class="H1242 s"> and the morning</span><span class="H259 s"> were the first</span><span class="H3117 s"> day</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (And the evening…: Heb. And the evening was, and the morning was)</span></div>
10_1	<div id="v10.1.6"><span class="H430 s">And God</span><span class="H559 s"> said</span><span class="H7549 s">, Let there be a firmament</span><span class="H8432 s"> in the midst</span><span class="H4325 s"> of the waters</span><span class="H914 s">, and let it divide</span><span class="H4325 s"> the waters</span><span class="H4325 s"> from the waters</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (firmament: Heb. expansion)</span></div>
10_1	<div id="v10.1.7"><span class="H430 s">And God</span><span class="H6213 s"> made</span><span class="H7549 s"> the firmament</span><span class="H914 s">, and divided</span><span class="H4325 s"> the waters</span><span class="H834 s"> which</span><span class="H8478 s"> <i>were</i> under</span><span class="H7549 s"> the firmament</span><span class="H4325 s"> from the waters</span><span class="H834 s"> which</span><span class="H5921 s"> <i>were</i> above</span><span class="H7549 s"> the firmament</span><span class="H3651 s">: and it was so</span>.</div>
10_1	<div id="v10.1.8"><span class="H430 s">And God</span><span class="H7121 s"> called</span><span class="H7549 s"> the firmament</span><span class="H8064 s"> Heaven</span><span class="H6153 s">. And the evening</span><span class="H1242 s"> and the morning</span><span class="H8145 s"> were the second</span><span class="H3117 s"> day</span>.</div>
10_1	<div id="v10.1.9"><span class="H430 s">And God</span><span class="H559 s"> said</span><span class="H4325 s">, Let the waters</span><span class="H8064 s"> under the heaven</span><span class="H6960 s"> be gathered together</span><span class="H413 s"> unto</span><span class="H259 s"> one</span><span class="H4725 s"> place</span><span class="H3004 s">, and let the dry</span><span class="H7200 s"> <i>land</i> appear</span>: and it was so.</div>
10_1	<div id="v10.1.10"><span class="H430 s">And God</span><span class="H7121 s"> called</span><span class="H3004 s"> the dry</span><span class="H776 s"> <i>land</i> Earth</span><span class="H4723 s">; and the gathering together</span><span class="H4325 s"> of the waters</span><span class="H7121 s"> called</span><span class="H3220 s"> he Seas</span><span class="H430 s">: and God</span><span class="H7200 s"> saw</span><span class="H2896 s"> that <i>it was</i> good</span>.</div>
10_1	<div id="v10.1.11"><span class="H430 s">And God</span><span class="H559 s"> said</span><span class="H776 s">, Let the earth</span><span class="H1876 s"> bring forth</span><span class="H1877 s"> grass</span><span class="H6212 s">, the herb</span><span class="H2232 s"> yielding</span><span class="H2233 s"> seed</span><span class="H6529 s">, <i>and</i> the fruit</span><span class="H6086 s"> tree</span><span class="H6213 s"> yielding</span><span class="H6529 s"> fruit</span><span class="H4327 s"> after his kind</span><span class="H834 s">, whose</span><span class="H2233 s"> seed</span><span class="H776 s"> <i>is</i> in itself, upon the earth</span>: and it was so. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (grass: Heb. tender grass)</span></div>
10_1	<div id="v10.1.12"><span class="H776 s">And the earth</span><span class="H3318 s"> brought forth</span><span class="H1877 s"> grass</span><span class="H6212 s">, <i>and</i> herb</span><span class="H2232 s"> yielding</span><span class="H2233 s"> seed</span><span class="H4327 s"> after his kind</span><span class="H6086 s">, and the tree</span><span class="H6213 s"> yielding</span><span class="H6529 s"> fruit</span><span class="H2233 s">, whose seed</span><span class="H4327 s"> <i>was</i> in itself, after his kind</span><span class="H430 s">: and God</span><span class="H7200 s"> saw</span><span class="H2896 s"> that <i>it was</i> good</span>.</div>
10_1	<div id="v10.1.13"><span class="H6153 s">And the evening</span><span class="H1242 s"> and the morning</span><span class="H7992 s"> were the third</span><span class="H3117 s"> day</span>.</div>
10_1	<div id="v10.1.14"><span class="H430 s">And God</span><span class="H559 s"> said</span><span class="H3974 s">, Let there be lights</span><span class="H7549 s"> in the firmament</span><span class="H8064 s"> of the heaven</span><span class="H914 s"> to divide</span><span class="H3117 s"> the day</span><span class="H3915 s"> from the night</span><span class="H226 s">; and let them be for signs</span><span class="H4150 s">, and for seasons</span><span class="H3117 s">, and for days</span><span class="H8141 s">, and years</span>: <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (the day…: Heb. between the day and between the night)</span></div>
10_1	<div id="v10.1.15"><span class="H3974 s">And let them be for lights</span><span class="H7549 s"> in the firmament</span><span class="H8064 s"> of the heaven</span><span class="H215 s"> to give light</span><span class="H776 s"> upon the earth</span>: and it was so.</div>
10_1	<div id="v10.1.16"><span class="H430 s">And God</span><span class="H6213 s"> made</span><span class="H8147 s"> two</span><span class="H1419 s"> great</span><span class="H3974 s"> lights</span><span class="H1419 s">; the greater</span><span class="H3974 s"> light</span><span class="H4475 s"> to rule</span><span class="H3117 s"> the day</span><span class="H6996 s">, and the lesser</span><span class="H3974 s"> light</span><span class="H4475 s"> to rule</span><span class="H3915 s"> the night</span><span class="H3556 s">: <i>he made</i> the stars</span> also. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (to rule the day…: Heb. for the rule of the day, etc.)</span></div>
10_1	<div id="v10.1.17"><span class="H430 s">And God</span><span class="H5414 s"> set</span><span class="H7549 s"> them in the firmament</span><span class="H8064 s"> of the heaven</span><span class="H215 s"> to give light</span><span class="H776 s"> upon the earth</span>,</div>
10_1	<div id="v10.1.18"><span class="H4910 s">And to rule</span><span class="H3117 s"> over the day</span><span class="H3915 s"> and over the night</span><span class="H914 s">, and to divide</span><span class="H216 s"> the light</span><span class="H2822 s"> from the darkness</span><span class="H430 s">: and God</span><span class="H7200 s"> saw</span><span class="H2896 s"> that <i>it was</i> good</span>.</div>
10_1	<div id="v10.1.19"><span class="H6153 s">And the evening</span><span class="H1242 s"> and the morning</span><span class="H7243 s"> were the fourth</span><span class="H3117 s"> day</span>.</div>
10_1	<div id="v10.1.20"><span class="H430 s">And God</span><span class="H559 s"> said</span><span class="H4325 s">, Let the waters</span><span class="H8317 s"> bring forth abundantly</span><span class="H8318 s"> the moving creature</span><span class="H2416 s"> that hath life</span><span class="H5315 s"> †</span><span class="H5775 s">, and fowl</span><span class="H5774 s"> <i>that</i> may fly</span><span class="H5921 s"> above</span><span class="H776 s"> the earth</span><span class="H6440 s"> in the open</span><span class="H7549 s"> firmament</span><span class="H8064 s"> of heaven</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (moving: or, creeping) (life: Heb. soul) (fowl…: Heb. let fowl fly) (open…: Heb. face of the firmament of heaven)</span></div>
10_1	<div id="v10.1.21"><span class="H430 s">And God</span><span class="H1254 s"> created</span><span class="H1419 s"> great</span><span class="H8577 s"> whales</span><span class="H2416 s">, and every living</span><span class="H5315 s"> creature</span><span class="H7430 s"> that moveth</span><span class="H4325 s">, which the waters</span><span class="H8317 s"> brought forth abundantly</span><span class="H4327 s">, after their kind</span><span class="H3671 s">, and every winged</span><span class="H5775 s"> fowl</span><span class="H4327 s"> after his kind</span><span class="H430 s">: and God</span><span class="H7200 s"> saw</span><span class="H2896 s"> that <i>it was</i> good</span>.</div>
10_1	<div id="v10.1.22"><span class="H430 s">And God</span><span class="H1288 s"> blessed</span><span class="H559 s"> them, saying</span><span class="H6509 s">, Be fruitful</span><span class="H7235 s">, and multiply</span><span class="H4390 s">, and fill</span><span class="H4325 s"> the waters</span><span class="H3220 s"> in the seas</span><span class="H5775 s">, and let fowl</span><span class="H7235 s"> multiply</span><span class="H776 s"> in the earth</span>.</div>
10_1	<div id="v10.1.23"><span class="H6153 s">And the evening</span><span class="H1242 s"> and the morning</span><span class="H2549 s"> were the fifth</span><span class="H3117 s"> day</span>.</div>
10_1	<div id="v10.1.24"><span class="H430 s">And God</span><span class="H559 s"> said</span><span class="H776 s">, Let the earth</span><span class="H3318 s"> bring forth</span><span class="H2416 s"> the living</span><span class="H5315 s"> creature</span><span class="H4327 s"> after his kind</span><span class="H929 s">, cattle</span><span class="H7431 s">, and creeping thing</span><span class="H2416 s">, and beast</span><span class="H776 s"> of the earth</span><span class="H4327 s"> after his kind</span>: and it was so.</div>
10_1	<div id="v10.1.25"><span class="H430 s">And God</span><span class="H6213 s"> made</span><span class="H2416 s"> the beast</span><span class="H776 s"> of the earth</span><span class="H4327 s"> after his kind</span><span class="H929 s">, and cattle</span><span class="H4327 s"> after their kind</span><span class="H7431 s">, and every thing that creepeth</span><span class="H127 s"> upon the earth</span><span class="H4327 s"> after his kind</span><span class="H430 s">: and God</span><span class="H7200 s"> saw</span><span class="H2896 s"> that <i>it was</i> good</span>.</div>
10_1	<div id="v10.1.26"><span class="H430 s">And God</span><span class="H559 s"> said</span><span class="H6213 s">, Let us make</span><span class="H120 s"> man</span><span class="H6754 s"> in our image</span><span class="H1823 s">, after our likeness</span><span class="H7287 s">: and let them have dominion</span><span class="H1710 s"> over the fish</span><span class="H3220 s"> of the sea</span><span class="H5775 s">, and over the fowl</span><span class="H8064 s"> of the air</span><span class="H929 s">, and over the cattle</span><span class="H776 s">, and over all the earth</span><span class="H7431 s">, and over every creeping thing</span><span class="H7430 s"> that creepeth</span><span class="H776 s"> upon the earth</span>.</div>
10_1	<div id="v10.1.27"><span class="H430 s">So God</span><span class="H1254 s"> created</span><span class="H120 s"> man</span><span class="H6754 s"> in his <i>own</i> image</span><span class="H6754 s">, in the image</span><span class="H430 s"> of God</span><span class="H1254 s"> created</span><span class="H2145 s"> he him; male</span><span class="H5347 s"> and female</span><span class="H1254 s"> created</span> he them.</div>
10_1	<div id="v10.1.28"><span class="H430 s">And God</span><span class="H1288 s"> blessed</span><span class="H430 s"> them, and God</span><span class="H559 s"> said</span><span class="H6509 s"> unto them, Be fruitful</span><span class="H7235 s">, and multiply</span><span class="H4390 s">, and replenish</span><span class="H776 s"> the earth</span><span class="H3533 s">, and subdue it</span><span class="H7287 s">: and have dominion</span><span class="H1710 s"> over the fish</span><span class="H3220 s"> of the sea</span><span class="H5775 s">, and over the fowl</span><span class="H8064 s"> of the air</span><span class="H2416 s">, and over every living thing</span><span class="H7430 s"> that moveth</span><span class="H776 s"> upon the earth</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (moveth: Heb. creepeth)</span></div>
10_1	<div id="v10.1.29"><span class="H430 s">And God</span><span class="H559 s"> said</span><span class="H2009 s">, Behold</span><span class="H5414 s">, I have given</span><span class="H6212 s"> you every herb</span><span class="H2232 s"> bearing</span><span class="H2233 s"> seed</span><span class="H6440 s">, which <i>is</i> upon the face</span><span class="H776 s"> of all the earth</span><span class="H6086 s">, and every tree</span><span class="H6529 s">, in the which <i>is</i> the fruit</span><span class="H6086 s"> of a tree</span><span class="H2232 s"> yielding</span><span class="H2233 s"> seed</span><span class="H1961 s">; to you it shall be</span><span class="H402 s"> for meat</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (bearing…: Heb. seeding seed) (yielding…: Heb. seeding seed)</span></div>
10_1	<div id="v10.1.30"><span class="H2416 s">And to every beast</span><span class="H776 s"> of the earth</span><span class="H5775 s">, and to every fowl</span><span class="H8064 s"> of the air</span><span class="H7430 s">, and to every thing that creepeth</span><span class="H776 s"> upon the earth</span><span class="H2416 s">, wherein <i>there is</i> life</span><span class="H5315 s"> †</span><span class="H3418 s">, <i>I have given</i> every green</span><span class="H6212 s"> herb</span><span class="H402 s"> for meat</span>: and it was so. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (life: Heb. a living soul)</span></div>
10_1	<div id="v10.1.31"><span class="H430 s">And God</span><span class="H7200 s"> saw</span><span class="H834 s"> every thing that</span><span class="H6213 s"> he had made</span><span class="H3966 s">, and, behold, <i>it was</i> very</span><span class="H2896 s"> good</span><span class="H6153 s">. And the evening</span><span class="H1242 s"> and the morning</span><span class="H8345 s"> were the sixth</span><span class="H3117 s"> day</span>.</div></div>
10_2	<div class="c10_2">
10_2	<div id="v10.2.1"><span class="H8064 s">Thus the heavens</span><span class="H776 s"> and the earth</span><span class="H3615 s"> were finished</span><span class="H6635 s">, and all the host of them</span>.</div>
10_2	<div id="v10.2.2"><span class="H7637 s">And on the seventh</span><span class="H3117 s"> day</span><span class="H430 s"> God</span><span class="H3615 s"> ended</span><span class="H4399 s"> his work</span><span class="H6213 s"> which he had made</span><span class="H7673 s">; and he rested</span><span class="H7637 s"> on the seventh</span><span class="H3117 s"> day</span><span class="H4399 s"> from all his work</span><span class="H6213 s"> which he had made</span>.</div>
10_2	<div id="v10.2.3"><span class="H430 s">And God</span><span class="H1288 s"> blessed</span><span class="H7637 s"> the seventh</span><span class="H3117 s"> day</span><span class="H6942 s">, and sanctified</span><span class="H3588 s"> it: because</span><span class="H7673 s"> that in it he had rested</span><span class="H4399 s"> from all his work</span><span class="H430 s"> which God</span><span class="H1254 s"> created</span><span class="H6213 s"> and made</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (created…: Heb. created to make)</span></div>
10_2	<div id="v10.2.4"><span class="H428 s">These</span><span class="H8435 s"> <i>are</i> the generations</span><span class="H8064 s"> of the heavens</span><span class="H776 s"> and of the earth</span><span class="H1254 s"> when they were created</span><span class="H3117 s">, in the day</span><span class="H3068 s"> that the LORD</span><span class="H430 s"> God</span><span class="H6213 s"> made</span><span class="H776 s"> the earth</span><span class="H8064 s"> and the heavens</span>,</div>
10_2	<div id="v10.2.5"><span class="H7880 s">And every plant</span><span class="H7704 s"> of the field</span><span class="H2962 s"> before</span><span class="H776 s"> it was in the earth</span><span class="H6212 s">, and every herb</span><span class="H7704 s"> of the field</span><span class="H2962 s"> before</span><span class="H6779 s"> it grew</span><span class="H3588 s">: for</span><span class="H3068 s"> the LORD</span><span class="H430 s"> God</span><span class="H3808 s"> had not</span><span class="H4305 s"> caused it to rain</span><span class="H776 s"> upon the earth</span><span class="H369 s">, and <i>there was</i> not</span><span class="H120 s"> a man</span><span class="H5647 s"> to till</span><span class="H127 s"> the ground</span>.</div>
10_2	<div id="v10.2.6"><span class="H5927 s">But there went up</span><span class="H108 s"> a mist</span><span class="H4480 s"> from</span><span class="H776 s"> the earth</span><span class="H8248 s">, and watered</span><span class="H6440 s"> the whole face</span><span class="H127 s"> of the ground</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (there…: or, a mist which went up from, etc.)</span></div>
10_2	<div id="v10.2.7"><span class="H3068 s">And the LORD</span><span class="H430 s"> God</span><span class="H3335 s"> formed</span><span class="H120 s"> man</span><span class="H6083 s"> <i>of</i> the dust</span><span class="H4480 s"> of</span><span class="H127 s"> the ground</span><span class="H5301 s">, and breathed</span><span class="H639 s"> into his nostrils</span><span class="H5397 s"> the breath</span><span class="H2416 s"> of life</span><span class="H120 s">; and man</span><span class="H2416 s"> became a living</span><span class="H5315 s"> soul</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (of the dust…: Heb. dust of the ground)</span></div>
10_2	<div id="v10.2.8"><span class="H3068 s">And the LORD</span><span class="H430 s"> God</span><span class="H5193 s"> planted</span><span class="H1588 s"> a garden</span><span class="H6924 s"> eastward</span><span class="H5731 s"> in Eden</span><span class="H8033 s">; and there</span><span class="H7760 s"> he put</span><span class="H120 s"> the man</span><span class="H834 s"> whom</span><span class="H3335 s"> he had formed</span>.</div>
10_2	<div id="v10.2.9"><span class="H4480 s">And out</span><span class="H127 s"> of the ground</span><span class="H6779 s"> made</span><span class="H3068 s"> the LORD</span><span class="H430 s"> God</span><span class="H6779 s"> to grow</span><span class="H6086 s"> every tree</span><span class="H2530 s"> that is pleasant</span><span class="H4758 s"> to the sight</span><span class="H2896 s">, and good</span><span class="H3978 s"> for food</span><span class="H6086 s">; the tree</span><span class="H2416 s"> of life</span><span class="H8432 s"> also in the midst</span><span class="H1588 s"> of the garden</span><span class="H6086 s">, and the tree</span><span class="H1847 s"> of knowledge</span><span class="H2896 s"> of good</span><span class="H7451 s"> and evil</span>.</div>
10_2	<div id="v10.2.10"><span class="H5104 s">And a river</span><span class="H3318 s"> went out</span><span class="H5731 s"> of Eden</span><span class="H8248 s"> to water</span><span class="H1588 s"> the garden</span><span class="H6504 s">; and from thence it was parted</span><span class="H702 s">, and became into four</span><span class="H7218 s"> heads</span>.</div>
10_2	<div id="v10.2.11"><span class="H8034 s">The name</span><span class="H259 s"> of the first</span><span class="H6376 s"> <i>is</i> Pison</span><span class="H1931 s">: that</span><span class="H5437 s"> <i>is</i> it which compasseth</span><span class="H776 s"> the whole land</span><span class="H2341 s"> of Havilah</span><span class="H834 s">, where</span><span class="H2091 s"> <i>there is</i> gold</span>;</div>
10_2	<div id="v10.2.12"><span class="H2091 s">And the gold</span><span class="H1931 s"> of that</span><span class="H776 s"> land</span><span class="H2896 s"> <i>is</i> good</span><span class="H916 s">: there <i>is</i> bdellium</span><span class="H7718 s"> and the onyx</span><span class="H68 s"> stone</span>.</div>
10_2	<div id="v10.2.13"><span class="H8034 s">And the name</span><span class="H8145 s"> of the second</span><span class="H5104 s"> river</span><span class="H1521 s"> <i>is</i> Gihon</span><span class="H5437 s">: the same <i>is</i> it that compasseth</span><span class="H776 s"> the whole land</span><span class="H3568 s"> of Ethiopia</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (Ethiopia: Heb. Cush)</span></div>
10_2	<div id="v10.2.14"><span class="H8034 s">And the name</span><span class="H7992 s"> of the third</span><span class="H5104 s"> river</span><span class="H2313 s"> <i>is</i> Hiddekel</span><span class="H1980 s">: that <i>is</i> it which goeth toward</span><span class="H6926 s"> the east</span><span class="H804 s"> of Assyria</span><span class="H7243 s">. And the fourth</span><span class="H5104 s"> river</span><span class="H6578 s"> <i>is</i> Euphrates</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (toward…: or, eastward to Assyria)</span></div>
10_2	<div id="v10.2.15"><span class="H3068 s">And the LORD</span><span class="H430 s"> God</span><span class="H3947 s"> took</span><span class="H120 s"> the man</span><span class="H3240 s">, and put him</span><span class="H1588 s"> into the garden</span><span class="H5731 s"> of Eden</span><span class="H5647 s"> to dress</span><span class="H8104 s"> it and to keep</span> it. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (the man: or, Adam)</span></div>
10_2	<div id="v10.2.16"><span class="H3068 s">And the LORD</span><span class="H430 s"> God</span><span class="H6680 s"> commanded</span><span class="H120 s"> the man</span><span class="H559 s">, saying</span><span class="H6086 s">, Of every tree</span><span class="H1588 s"> of the garden</span><span class="H398 s"> thou mayest freely</span><span class="H398 s"> eat</span>: <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (thou…: Heb. eating thou shalt eat)</span></div>
10_2	<div id="v10.2.17"><span class="H6086 s">But of the tree</span><span class="H1847 s"> of the knowledge</span><span class="H2896 s"> of good</span><span class="H7451 s"> and evil</span><span class="H398 s">, thou shalt not eat</span><span class="H3117 s"> of it: for in the day</span><span class="H398 s"> that thou eatest</span><span class="H4191 s"> thereof thou shalt surely</span><span class="H4191 s"> die</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (thou shalt surely…: Heb. dying thou shalt die)</span></div>
10_2	<div id="v10.2.18"><span class="H3068 s">And the LORD</span><span class="H430 s"> God</span><span class="H559 s"> said</span><span class="H2896 s">, <i>It is</i> not good</span><span class="H120 s"> that the man</span><span class="H1961 s"> should be</span><span class="H6213 s"> alone; I will make</span><span class="H5828 s"> him an help meet</span> for him. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (meet…: Heb. as before him)</span></div>
10_2	<div id="v10.2.19"><span class="H127 s">And out of the ground</span><span class="H3068 s"> the LORD</span><span class="H430 s"> God</span><span class="H3335 s"> formed</span><span class="H2416 s"> every beast</span><span class="H7704 s"> of the field</span><span class="H5775 s">, and every fowl</span><span class="H8064 s"> of the air</span><span class="H935 s">; and brought</span><span class="H120 s"> <i>them</i> unto Adam</span><span class="H7200 s"> to see</span><span class="H7121 s"> what he would call</span><span class="H120 s"> them: and whatsoever Adam</span><span class="H7121 s"> called</span><span class="H2416 s"> every living</span><span class="H5315 s"> creature</span><span class="H1931 s">, that</span><span class="H8034 s"> <i>was</i> the name thereof</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (Adam: or, the man)</span></div>
10_2	<div id="v10.2.20"><span class="H120 s">And Adam</span><span class="H7121 s"> gave</span><span class="H8034 s"> names</span><span class="H929 s"> to all cattle</span><span class="H5775 s">, and to the fowl</span><span class="H8064 s"> of the air</span><span class="H2416 s">, and to every beast</span><span class="H7704 s"> of the field</span><span class="H120 s">; but for Adam</span><span class="H4672 s"> there was not found</span><span class="H5828 s"> an help meet</span> for him. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (gave: Heb. called)</span></div>
10_2	<div id="v10.2.21"><span class="H3068 s">And the LORD</span><span class="H430 s"> God</span><span class="H5307 s"> caused</span><span class="H8639 s"> a deep sleep</span><span class="H5307 s"> to fall</span><span class="H121 s"> upon Adam</span><span class="H3462 s">, and he slept</span><span class="H3947 s">: and he took</span><span class="H259 s"> one</span><span class="H6763 s"> of his ribs</span><span class="H5462 s">, and closed up</span><span class="H1320 s"> the flesh</span> instead thereof;</div>
10_2	<div id="v10.2.22"><span class="H6763 s">And the rib</span><span class="H3068 s">, which the LORD</span><span class="H430 s"> God</span><span class="H3947 s"> had taken</span><span class="H120 s"> from man</span><span class="H1129 s">, made</span><span class="H802 s"> he a woman</span><span class="H935 s">, and brought</span><span class="H120 s"> her unto the man</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (made: Heb. builded)</span></div>
10_2	<div id="v10.2.23"><span class="H120 s">And Adam</span><span class="H559 s"> said</span><span class="H2063 s">, This</span><span class="H6471 s"> <i>is</i> now</span><span class="H6106 s"> bone</span><span class="H6106 s"> of my bones</span><span class="H1320 s">, and flesh</span><span class="H1320 s"> of my flesh</span><span class="H2063 s">: she</span><span class="H7121 s"> shall be called</span><span class="H802 s"> Woman</span><span class="H2063 s">, because she</span><span class="H3947 s"> was taken</span><span class="H376 s"> out of Man</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (Woman: Heb. Isha) (Man: Heb. Ish)</span></div>
10_2	<div id="v10.2.24"><span class="H3651 s">Therefore</span><span class="H376 s"> shall a man</span><span class="H5800 s"> leave</span><span class="H1 s"> his father</span><span class="H517 s"> and his mother</span><span class="H1692 s">, and shall cleave</span><span class="H802 s"> unto his wife</span><span class="H259 s">: and they shall be one</span><span class="H1320 s"> flesh</span>.</div>
10_2	<div id="v10.2.25"><span class="H8147 s">And they were both</span><span class="H6174 s"> naked</span><span class="H120 s">, the man</span><span class="H802 s"> and his wife</span><span class="H954 s">, and were not ashamed</span>.</div></div>
10_3	<div class="c10_3">
10_3	<div id="v10.3.1"><span class="H5175 s">Now the serpent</span><span class="H1961 s"> was</span><span class="H6175 s"> more subtil</span><span class="H2416 s"> than any beast</span><span class="H7704 s"> of the field</span><span class="H3068 s"> which the LORD</span><span class="H430 s"> God</span><span class="H6213 s"> had made</span><span class="H559 s">. And he said</span><span class="H802 s"> unto the woman</span><span class="H637 s">, Yea</span><span class="H430 s">, hath God</span><span class="H559 s"> said</span><span class="H398 s">, Ye shall not eat</span><span class="H6086 s"> of every tree</span><span class="H1588 s"> of the garden</span>? <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (Yea…: Heb. Yea, because, etc.)</span></div>
10_3	<div id="v10.3.2"><span class="H802 s">And the woman</span><span class="H559 s"> said</span><span class="H5175 s"> unto the serpent</span><span class="H398 s">, We may eat</span><span class="H6529 s"> of the fruit</span><span class="H6086 s"> of the trees</span><span class="H1588 s"> of the garden</span>:</div>
10_3	<div id="v10.3.3"><span class="H6529 s">But of the fruit</span><span class="H6086 s"> of the tree</span><span class="H8432 s"> which <i>is</i> in the midst</span><span class="H1588 s"> of the garden</span><span class="H430 s">, God</span><span class="H559 s"> hath said</span><span class="H398 s">, Ye shall not eat</span><span class="H5060 s"> of it, neither shall ye touch</span><span class="H6435 s"> it, lest</span><span class="H4191 s"> ye die</span>.</div>
10_3	<div id="v10.3.4"><span class="H5175 s">And the serpent</span><span class="H559 s"> said</span><span class="H802 s"> unto the woman</span><span class="H4191 s">, Ye shall not surely</span><span class="H4191 s"> die</span>:</div>
10_3	<div id="v10.3.5"><span class="H430 s">For God</span><span class="H3045 s"> doth know</span><span class="H3117 s"> that in the day</span><span class="H398 s"> ye eat</span><span class="H5869 s"> thereof, then your eyes</span><span class="H6491 s"> shall be opened</span><span class="H430 s">, and ye shall be as gods</span><span class="H3045 s">, knowing</span><span class="H2896 s"> good</span><span class="H7451 s"> and evil</span>.</div>
10_3	<div id="v10.3.6"><span class="H802 s">And when the woman</span><span class="H7200 s"> saw</span><span class="H6086 s"> that the tree</span><span class="H2896 s"> <i>was</i> good</span><span class="H3978 s"> for food</span><span class="H1931 s">, and that it</span><span class="H8378 s"> <i>was</i> pleasant</span><span class="H5869 s"> to the eyes</span><span class="H6086 s">, and a tree</span><span class="H2530 s"> to be desired</span><span class="H7919 s"> to make <i>one</i> wise</span><span class="H3947 s">, she took</span><span class="H6529 s"> of the fruit thereof</span><span class="H398 s">, and did eat</span><span class="H5414 s">, and gave</span><span class="H1571 s"> also</span><span class="H376 s"> unto her husband</span><span class="H398 s"> with her; and he did eat</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (pleasant: Heb. a desire)</span></div>
10_3	<div id="v10.3.7"><span class="H5869 s">And the eyes</span><span class="H8147 s"> of them both</span><span class="H6491 s"> were opened</span><span class="H1992 s">, and they</span><span class="H3045 s"> knew</span><span class="H5903 s"> that they <i>were</i> naked</span><span class="H8609 s">; and they sewed</span><span class="H8384 s"> fig</span><span class="H5929 s"> leaves</span><span class="H8609 s"> together</span><span class="H6213 s">, and made themselves</span><span class="H2290 s"> aprons</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (aprons: or, things to gird about)</span></div>
10_3	<div id="v10.3.8"><span class="H8085 s">And they heard</span><span class="H6963 s"> the voice</span><span class="H3068 s"> of the LORD</span><span class="H430 s"> God</span><span class="H1980 s"> walking</span><span class="H1588 s"> in the garden</span><span class="H7307 s"> in the cool</span><span class="H3117 s"> of the day</span><span class="H120 s">: and Adam</span><span class="H802 s"> and his wife</span><span class="H2244 s"> hid themselves</span><span class="H6440 s"> from the presence</span><span class="H3068 s"> of the LORD</span><span class="H430 s"> God</span><span class="H8432 s"> amongst</span><span class="H6086 s"> the trees</span><span class="H1588 s"> of the garden</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (cool: Heb. wind)</span></div>
10_3	<div id="v10.3.9"><span class="H3068 s">And the LORD</span><span class="H430 s"> God</span><span class="H7121 s"> called</span><span class="H120 s"> unto Adam</span><span class="H559 s">, and said</span><span class="H335 s"> unto him, Where <i>art</i> thou</span>?</div>
10_3	<div id="v10.3.10"><span class="H559 s">And he said</span><span class="H8085 s">, I heard</span><span class="H6963 s"> thy voice</span><span class="H1588 s"> in the garden</span><span class="H3372 s">, and I was afraid</span><span class="H595 s">, because I</span><span class="H5903 s"> <i>was</i> naked</span><span class="H2244 s">; and I hid myself</span>.</div>
10_3	<div id="v10.3.11"><span class="H559 s">And he said</span><span class="H4310 s">, Who</span><span class="H5046 s"> told</span><span class="H5903 s"> thee that thou <i>wast</i> naked</span><span class="H398 s">? Hast thou eaten</span><span class="H6086 s"> of the tree</span><span class="H6680 s">, whereof I commanded thee</span><span class="H1115 s"> that thou shouldest not</span><span class="H398 s"> eat</span>?</div>
10_3	<div id="v10.3.12"><span class="H120 s">And the man</span><span class="H559 s"> said</span><span class="H802 s">, The woman</span><span class="H5414 s"> whom thou gavest</span><span class="H5978 s"> <i>to be</i> with me</span><span class="H1931 s">, she</span><span class="H5414 s"> gave</span><span class="H6086 s"> me of the tree</span><span class="H398 s">, and I did eat</span>.</div>
10_3	<div id="v10.3.13"><span class="H3068 s">And the LORD</span><span class="H430 s"> God</span><span class="H559 s"> said</span><span class="H802 s"> unto the woman</span><span class="H6213 s">, What <i>is</i> this <i>that</i> thou hast done</span><span class="H802 s">? And the woman</span><span class="H559 s"> said</span><span class="H5175 s">, The serpent</span><span class="H5377 s"> beguiled me</span><span class="H398 s">, and I did eat</span>.</div>
10_3	<div id="v10.3.14"><span class="H3068 s">And the LORD</span><span class="H430 s"> God</span><span class="H559 s"> said</span><span class="H5175 s"> unto the serpent</span><span class="H859 s">, Because thou</span><span class="H6213 s"> hast done</span><span class="H779 s"> this, thou <i>art</i> cursed</span><span class="H929 s"> above all cattle</span><span class="H2416 s">, and above every beast</span><span class="H7704 s"> of the field</span><span class="H1512 s">; upon thy belly</span><span class="H3212 s"> shalt thou go</span><span class="H6083 s">, and dust</span><span class="H398 s"> shalt thou eat</span><span class="H3117 s"> all the days</span><span class="H2416 s"> of thy life</span>:</div>
10_3	<div id="v10.3.15"><span class="H7896 s">And I will put</span><span class="H342 s"> enmity</span><span class="H802 s"> between thee and the woman</span><span class="H2233 s">, and between thy seed</span><span class="H2233 s"> and her seed</span><span class="H7779 s">; it shall bruise</span><span class="H7218 s"> thy head</span><span class="H7779 s">, and thou shalt bruise</span><span class="H6119 s"> his heel</span>.</div>
10_3	<div id="v10.3.16"><span class="H802 s">Unto the woman</span><span class="H559 s"> he said</span><span class="H7235 s">, I will greatly</span><span class="H7235 s"> multiply</span><span class="H6093 s"> thy sorrow</span><span class="H2032 s"> and thy conception</span><span class="H6089 s">; in sorrow</span><span class="H3205 s"> thou shalt bring forth</span><span class="H1121 s"> children</span><span class="H8669 s">; and thy desire</span><span class="H376 s"> <i>shall be</i> to thy husband</span><span class="H4910 s">, and he shall rule</span> over thee. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (to thy…: or, subject to thy husband)</span></div>
10_3	<div id="v10.3.17"><span class="H121 s">And unto Adam</span><span class="H559 s"> he said</span><span class="H8085 s">, Because thou hast hearkened</span><span class="H6963 s"> unto the voice</span><span class="H802 s"> of thy wife</span><span class="H398 s">, and hast eaten</span><span class="H6086 s"> of the tree</span><span class="H834 s">, of which</span><span class="H6680 s"> I commanded thee</span><span class="H559 s">, saying</span><span class="H398 s">, Thou shalt not eat</span><span class="H779 s"> of it: cursed</span><span class="H127 s"> <i>is</i> the ground</span><span class="H6093 s"> for thy sake; in sorrow</span><span class="H398 s"> shalt thou eat</span><span class="H3605 s"> <i>of</i> it all</span><span class="H3117 s"> the days</span><span class="H2416 s"> of thy life</span>;</div>
10_3	<div id="v10.3.18"><span class="H6975 s">Thorns also</span><span class="H1863 s"> and thistles</span><span class="H6779 s"> shall it bring forth</span><span class="H398 s"> to thee; and thou shalt eat</span><span class="H6212 s"> the herb</span><span class="H7704 s"> of the field</span>; <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (bring…: Heb. cause to bud)</span></div>
10_3	<div id="v10.3.19"><span class="H2188 s">In the sweat</span><span class="H639 s"> of thy face</span><span class="H398 s"> shalt thou eat</span><span class="H3899 s"> bread</span><span class="H5704 s">, till</span><span class="H7725 s"> thou return</span><span class="H127 s"> unto the ground</span><span class="H3947 s">; for out of it wast thou taken</span><span class="H6083 s">: for dust</span><span class="H859 s"> thou</span><span class="H6083 s"> <i>art</i>, and unto dust</span><span class="H7725 s"> shalt thou return</span>.</div>
10_3	<div id="v10.3.20"><span class="H120 s">And Adam</span><span class="H7121 s"> called</span><span class="H802 s"> his wife's</span><span class="H8034 s"> name</span><span class="H2332 s"> Eve</span><span class="H517 s">; because she was the mother</span><span class="H2416 s"> of all living</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (Eve: Heb. Chavah: that is Living)</span></div>
10_3	<div id="v10.3.21"><span class="H120 s">Unto Adam</span><span class="H802 s"> also and to his wife</span><span class="H3068 s"> did the LORD</span><span class="H430 s"> God</span><span class="H6213 s"> make</span><span class="H3801 s"> coats</span><span class="H5785 s"> of skins</span><span class="H3847 s">, and clothed them</span>.</div>
10_3	<div id="v10.3.22"><span class="H3068 s">And the LORD</span><span class="H430 s"> God</span><span class="H559 s"> said</span><span class="H2005 s">, Behold</span><span class="H120 s">, the man</span><span class="H259 s"> is become as one</span><span class="H3045 s"> of us, to know</span><span class="H2896 s"> good</span><span class="H7451 s"> and evil</span><span class="H7971 s">: and now, lest he put forth</span><span class="H3027 s"> his hand</span><span class="H3947 s">, and take</span><span class="H6086 s"> also of the tree</span><span class="H2416 s"> of life</span><span class="H398 s">, and eat</span><span class="H2425 s">, and live</span><span class="H5769 s"> for ever</span>:</div>
10_3	<div id="v10.3.23"><span class="H3068 s">Therefore the LORD</span><span class="H430 s"> God</span><span class="H7971 s"> sent him forth</span><span class="H1588 s"> from the garden</span><span class="H5731 s"> of Eden</span><span class="H5647 s">, to till</span><span class="H127 s"> the ground</span><span class="H3947 s"> from whence he was taken</span>.</div>
10_3	<div id="v10.3.24"><span class="H1644 s">So he drove out</span><span class="H120 s"> the man</span><span class="H7931 s">; and he placed</span><span class="H6924 s"> at the east</span><span class="H1588 s"> of the garden</span><span class="H5731 s"> of Eden</span><span class="H3742 s"> Cherubims</span><span class="H3858 s">, and a flaming</span><span class="H2719 s"> sword</span><span class="H2015 s"> which turned every way</span><span class="H8104 s">, to keep</span><span class="H1870 s"> the way</span><span class="H6086 s"> of the tree</span><span class="H2416 s"> of life</span>.</div></div>